Task 8
Array
Task 1:
Create an array of integers.Find the sum and average of all elements in the array.
public class ArraySumAverage {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Create an array 
        int[] numbers = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};
        
        // Initialize variables  sum and average
        int sum = 0;
        double average;
        for (int number : numbers) {
            sum += number;
        }

        // Calculate the average
        average = (double) sum / numbers.length;

        // Print the sum and average
        System.out.println("Sum of array elements: " + sum);
        System.out.println("Average of array elements: " + average);
    }
}

Task 2:
Implement a program to find the maximum and minimum values in an integer array.
public class ArrayMaxMin {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Create an array of integers
        int[] numbers = {15, 42, 8, 23, 67, 4, 99};
        int max = numbers[0];
        int min = numbers[0];
// Loop through the array to find max and min values
        for (int number : numbers) {
            if (number > max) {
                max = number; // Update max if a larger value is found
            }
            if (number < min) {
                min = number; // Update min if a smaller value is found
            }
        }
        System.out.println("Maximum value in the array: " + max);
        System.out.println("Minimum value in the array: " + min);
    }
}
Task 3:
public class MatrixPrinter {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Create a 2D array (matrix)
        int[][] matrix = {
            {1, 2, 3},
            {4, 5, 6},
            {7, 8, 9}
        };

        // Print the matrix in a well-formatted manner
        System.out.println("The matrix is:");
        for (int i = 0; i < matrix.length; i++) { // Iterate over rows
            for (int j = 0; j < matrix[i].length; j++) { // Iterate over columns
                System.out.print(matrix[i][j] + "\t"); // Print each element with a tab
            }
            System.out.println(); // Move to the next line after printing a row
        }
    }
}
Create a two-dimensional array to represent a matrix. Write a program to print the matrix in a well-formatted manner.
public class MatrixPrinter {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        int[][] matrix = {
            {1, 2, 3},
            {4, 5, 6},
            {7, 8, 9}
        };
        System.out.println("The matrix is:");
        for (int i = 0; i < matrix.length; i++) { // Iterate over rows
            for (int j = 0; j < matrix[i].length; j++) { // Iterate over columns
                System.out.print(matrix[i][j] + "\t"); // Print each element with a tab
            }
            System.out.println(); // Move to the next line after printing a row
        }
    }
}



